'''愚昧'''(Foolishness)是指人缺乏足夠的[[智慧|智慧]]以作出最適當而小心的選擇。某程度上，他是與[[愚蠢|愚蠢]]不同，因[[愚蠢|愚蠢]]與[[智力|智力]]的關係較大<ref>{{citation |title=Why Smart People Can Be So Stupid |author=Robert J. Sternberg |chapter=Smart People Are Not Stupid, But They Sure Can Be Foolish |pages=232 et seq. |publisher=[[Yale_University_Press|Yale University Press]] |year=2003 |isbn=9780300101706}}</ref>。愚昧的人也稱為愚人，[[愚人節|愚人節]]便是作弄這些人的一年一度節日。人們時常製作假新聞欺騙那些輕信別人、不仔細分析事物及真偽的人。
在[[使徒保羅|使徒保羅]]的[[哥林多前書|哥林多前書]]中，他將「愚昧」與「智慧」作為相對。他鄙視那種驕傲自大的人，並提倡對愚昧要以謙虛的態度。[[柏拉圖|柏拉圖]]亦說過:「他是最具[[智慧|智慧]]的人因他自知自己缺乏對智慧的認識」，但保羅對智慧的理解與柏拉圖的不同<ref>{{citation |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=8swIKfGhcUsC&pg=PA305 |title=Critiqe of religion and philosophy |author=Walter Arnold Kaufmann |accessdate=2015-04-07 |archive-date=2012-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114173121/http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=8swIKfGhcUsC&pg=PA305 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=eLqvm8PqyCMC&pg=PA40 |title=The Letters to the Corinthians |author=William Barclay |accessdate=2015-04-07 |archive-date=2012-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114173143/http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=eLqvm8PqyCMC&pg=PA40 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

